&lt;p&gt;Despite the closer bond between a mother and her son, the illogical distribution of shares dictated by the Quran results in the sister receiving a larger inheritance portion than the mother (even if the sister is married).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, the widow's share is even smaller than that of the mother, while the sister's share becomes even more substantial.&lt;/p&gt;
